node.text: Today is international Tiger Day - to celebrate we introduce you to some of our tiger team and beautiful big cats. Sadly, tiger numbers a dwindling in the wild, and the work we do here at Australia Zoo helps conserve these beautiful animals. Click here to read more about out tiger conservation: https://wildlifewarriors.org.au/conservation-projects/sumatran-tigers

node.title: Meet Our Tiger Keepers | Australia Zoo Life

node.text: Wishing the happiest birthday to our ultimate Wildlife Warrior, Terri! Your strength and perseverance has lead #AustraliaZoo and @wildlifewarriorsworldwide to accomplish milestones in the world of wildlife conservation. Thank you for working every single day to ensure Steve's passion and legacy continues. We love you! 💖

node.text: It's Father's Day weekend in the USA! Join the Irwins as they share stories about their Dads and reminisce on some special times. It's an extra special day as it's Chandler's very first Father's Day! Wishing all the Dads in the USA a very Happy Father's Day!

node.text:
Crikey! We wanted to send a big thank you to the family at @hoselinkofficial for helping us care for our world-class zoological gardens connecting our guests to nature.

Thank you for your support, making a difference in wildlife conservation! Check out the Cultivating Connections series featuring some of our favourite Australia Zoo animals!
#hoselink #cultivatingconnections

node.title: Hoselink Cultivating Connections with Australia Zoo

node.text: “On my evening motorbike ride I found this turtle a bit hung up in the fence next to a road and an alligator enclosure (not a safe place to be when you’re a little turtle!) So I took him for a ride on the bike and relocated him to a nearby waterhole. Hopefully Sheldon appreciated the rescue!” — @robertirwinphotography

node.text: Congratulations to our guests, Jesse and Erin, who popped the big question in the Crocoseum🎉 Are you planning that special moment this year? We’re here to help make it magical! From proposals to elopements, visit australiazoo.com.au and let the Crikey Crew help you say “I do!” ❤️ (Feel free to tag anyone who could use a little hint😊💍 )

node.text: Thank you for your extraordinary support during this profound year. As we embark on 2021, we are grateful for every joyful moment shared here at #AustraliaZoo. Wishing you a safe and happy New Year from the entire Australia Zoo Crew! 🎉

node.text: Did you hear the news? The #AustraliaZoo Wildlife Hospital has officially treated over 100,000 patients. We are proud to be giving our native wildlife a second chance at life. You can visit www.wildlifewarriors.org for more information💚

node.text: Today is international Tiger Day - to celebrate we introduce you to some of our tiger team and beautiful big cats. Sadly, tiger numbers a dwindling in the wild, and the work we do here at Australia Zoo helps conserve these beautiful animals. Click here to read more about out tiger conservation: https://wildlifewarriors.org.au/conservation-projects/sumatran-tigers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia Zoo on July 28, 2021. May be an image of big cat and nature.

node.text:
Happy #InternationalTigerDay from our #AustraliaZoo family to yours. We’re proud to give critically endangered Sumatran tigers a helping hand with our breeding program and supporting anti-poaching units in Sumatra. 
 
Thanks to @samsungau , guests can support these essential programs by tapping their phones or cards to donate while visiting our amazing Sumatran tiger ambassadors at Australia Zoo! They will even see a special thank you from Robert on The Terrace 65” Outdoor TV.

node.text: Only one more cat nap until International Tiger Day!🐯 We will see you at #AustraliaZoo for a “cat-astic” day filled with a celebration of these gorgeous animals while raising funds and awareness for our conservation projects protecting tigers in Sumatra. We’re “feline” excited!

node.text: “Flick the swamp wallaby joey was found in his mum’s pouch after being hit by a car. Sadly, his mum didn’t make it, leaving poor Flick behind who was then diagnosed with pneumonia, struggling to breathe. With expert care from our vet team at the #AustraliaZoo Wildlife Hospital and a specialised wildlife carer, this adorable little one is doing much better and is well on his way to recovery. 💛” — @wildlifewarriorsworldwide
